explanation: This solution utilizes dynamic programming and bit manipulation to count the number of 1's in the binary representation of each number from 0 to n in a single pass. The expression `ans[i >> 1]` reuses the count of 1's from the parent node (i/2) and `(i & 1)` adds 1 if the current bit is 1, effectively achieving a linear time complexity.

